      "content": "The 95% confidence interval for the main efficacy projection currently sits between 78% and 84%, which accounts for the observed variance. Compared to our historical models, the standard deviation on the primary endpoint is slightly higher, registering at 0.8 standard deviations above the baseline prediction. Although it slightly widens the margin of error, the current model calibration suggests this deviation remains within acceptable risk thresholds for the budget review.",
      "source": "target",
