      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Frankly, if you examine the raw telemetry from the last three weeks, the trend indicates a slight, but persistent, downward drift in the secondary biomarker response. While the primary efficacy is still robustly within the projected range, accurately stating the unvarnished truth is that the tail end of the data suggests a potential risk of the lower end of the confidence interval being breached. I recommend flagging the sensitivity analysis that tests a flatter dose response curve before the budget meeting.",
